Weddings/Celebrations

Kathleen Shattuck, George Markov

By VINCENT M. MALLOZZIOCT. 21, 2012



Continue reading the main story
Share This Page

Continue reading the main story









Kathleen Elizabeth Shattuck, the daughter of Jennifer W. Budge of Carmel, Calif., and Mayo A. Shattuck III of Baltimore, was married Saturday to George Stillanov Markov, a son of Dr. Diana D. Markov and Stilian G. Markov of Sofia, Bulgaria. The Rev. Michael Marini, a Roman Catholic priest, performed the ceremony at the Santa Catalina Rosary Chapel in Monterey, Calif.The couple met at Stanford, from which they each received an M.B.A.Until last month, the bride, 29, was a senior product manager in San Francisco at SCIenergy, which provides energy management software. She serves on the San Francisco board of Reading Partner, a nonprofit organization that provides volunteer tutoring to children. She graduated from Williams College.Her father, who works in Baltimore, is the chairman of Exelon Corp, a Chicago-based utility. He is also chairman of the Institute of Nuclear Power Operations, which is based in Atlanta. Her mother retired as the executive director of Ladew Topiary Gardens, a historical home and botanical garden in Monkton, Md.

Advertisement

Continue reading the main story

The groom, 33, is an investment analyst at White Elm Capital, a hedge fund based in Greenwich, Conn. He graduated from Colgate University. Continue reading the main story







Advertisement

Continue reading the main story





His mother is a pediatrician in private practice in Sofia. His father is an electrical engineer with Gemamex, a distributor of electric equipment in Sofia.
Photo







Credit
            Scott Campbell Photography        


The couple met in April 2009, one month before Mr. Markov graduated from Stanford and moved to New York.“I thought he was very smart, very funny and very nice, and we just sort of clicked,” said Ms. Shattuck, who was one academic year behind Mr. Markov. “It was frustrating to finally meet someone I could see a future with, but to know that it probably wouldn’t last because he was moving across the country.”Still, they decided to give their brief, newfound love a chance by embarking on a long-distance relationship.
