“We both realized it wasn’t very practical,” Ms. Shattuck said, “but we also realized it was worth pursuing.”Their next two years were filled with coast-to-coast trips. They also took trips to India, Greece, Turkey and Bulgaria, where Mr. Markov’s family lives.He proposed in New York in December 2011, at the Helmsley Park Lane Hotel. He surprised her with an engagement ring, as well as tickets to the Broadway show “Wicked.”“It was the happiest moment of my life,” Mr. Markov said. “Looking back, I’m ecstatic that we stayed the course.” VINCENT M. MALLOZZI
