Background

		Mr. Mayo A. Shattuck, III, serves as Special Advisor at US Fiduciary, Inc. Mr. Shattuck serves as a Member of the Executive Board at MidOcean Partners. He served as the Co-Head of Global Investment Banking-Group Division at Deutsche Bank Trust Corporation. He served as the Chief Executive Officer and President at Constellation Energy Group, Inc. at Constellation Energy Nuclear Group, LLC, from November 2001 to March 14, 2012 and served as its Executive Chairman from ... July 2002 to March 14, 2012. He served as the Co-Chief Executive Officer and Co-Chairman of DB Alex. Brown LLC and Deutsche Banc Securities Inc., from June 1999 to October 2001. From 1991 to 1997, Mr. Shattuck served as President and Chief Operating Officer and a Director of Alex Brown Inc., which merged with Bankers Trust in September 1997. He served as Executive Chairman of Exelon Corporation from March 12, 2012 to February 28, 2013. He also served as the Global Head of Private Banking at Deutsche Banc Alex. Brown. Mr. Shattuck serves as the Chairman of the Board of Visitors of the University of Maryland, Baltimore County. He has been the Non-Executive Chairman of Exelon Corporation since March 1, 2013. He is a Member of the Board of Edison Electric Institute. He has been an Independent Director of The Gap, Inc. since 2002. He has been an Independent Director of Capital One Financial Corporation and Exelon Corporation since October 31, 2003 and since April 23, 2013 respectively. He has been a Director of Alarm.Com Holdings, Inc. since May 2014, where he previously served as its Director from March 12, 2012 to February 28, 2013. He serves as a Member of Advisory Board of Rosewood Capital. He serves as a Director of C3, LLC, C3 Energy, Inc., C3, Inc. He serves as a Director of Nuclear Energy Institute and Institute of Nuclear Power Operations. Mr. Shattuck serves as a Member of the Board of Trustees of John Hopkins Medicine and a Member of the Advisory Council of Stanford Graduate School of Business. He serves as a Board Member of the Walters Art Meusum. He served as the Chairman of Baltimore Gas and Electric Company from July 2002 to April 2007. He served as Vice Chairman and Director of Deutsche Bank Trust Corporation from 1997 to June 1999. Mr. Shattuck served as an Executive Director of Constellation Energy Group, Inc., form May 1999 to March 12, 2012. He served as a Director of Baltimore Gas and Electric Company. He served as a Director of Deutsche Bank Alex. Brown Inc. from 1991 to 1997, Constellation Enterprises Inc., from March 1998 to May 1999 and at Constellation Holdings, Inc. from January 1994 to March 1998. He received an Honorary Doctor of Public Service Degree from the University of Maryland Baltimore County. Mr. Shattuck holds an M.B.A. from Stanford University, where he graduated as an Arjay Miller Scholar and a B.A. from Williams College.Read Full Background




